#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.61"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.61:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.61:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.61:0.3"
msgid "61. Majjhesutta"
msgstr "61. In the Middle"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an6.61:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an6.61:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Benares, in the deer park at "
"Isipatana."

msgctxt "an6.61:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulānaṃ therānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkantānaṃ maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ "
"ayamantarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time, after the meal, on return from alms-round, several senior "
"mendicants sat together in the pavilion and this discussion came up among "
"them:"

msgctxt "an6.61:1.4"
msgid "“vuttamidaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā pārāyane metteyyapañhe:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, this was said by the Buddha in ‘The Way to the Beyond’, in ‘The "
"Questions of Metteyya’:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:2.1"
msgid "‘Yo ubhonte viditvāna,"
msgstr "‘The sage has known both ends,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: na lippati → na limpati (s2, s3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.61:2.2"
msgid "majjhe mantā na lippati;"
msgstr "and is not stuck in the middle."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.61:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ brūmi mahāpurisoti,"
msgstr "He is a great man, I declare,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sibbini → sibbani (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.61:2.4"
msgid "sodha sibbini maccagā’”ti."
msgstr "he has escaped the seamstress here.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.400"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Katamo nu kho, āvuso, eko anto, katamo dutiyo anto, kiṃ majjhe, kā "
"sibbinī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"But what is one end? What’s the second end? What’s the middle? And who is "
"the seamstress?”"

msgctxt "an6.61:3.2"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:3.3"
msgid ""
"“phasso kho, āvuso, eko anto, phassasamudayo dutiyo anto, phassanirodho "
"majjhe, taṇhā sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“Contact, reverends, is one end. The origin of contact is the second end. "
"The cessation of contact is the middle. And craving is the seamstress,"

msgctxt "an6.61:3.4"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr "for craving weaves one to rebirth in this or that state of existence."

#. VAR: abhijānanto → abhijānitvā (mr)
#. VAR: parijānanto → parijānitvā (mr)
msgctxt "an6.61:3.5"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ parijānāti, "
"abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows what should be directly known and "
"completely understands what should be completely understood. Knowing and "
"understanding thus they make an end of suffering in this very life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:4.2"
msgid ""
"“atītaṃ kho, āvuso, eko anto, anāgataṃ dutiyo anto, paccuppannaṃ majjhe, "
"taṇhā sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“The past, reverends, is one end. The future is the second end. The present "
"is the middle. And craving is the seamstress …"

msgctxt "an6.61:4.3"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.61:4.4"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ parijānāti, "
"abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto, pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows … an end of suffering in this very "
"life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:5.2"
msgid ""
"“sukhā, āvuso, vedanā eko anto, dukkhā vedanā dutiyo anto, adukkhamasukhā "
"vedanā majjhe, taṇhā sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“Pleasant feeling, reverends, is one end. Painful feeling is the second end. "
"Neutral feeling is the middle. And craving is the seamstress …"

msgctxt "an6.61:5.3"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.61:5.4"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ parijānāti, "
"abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto, pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows … an end of suffering in this very "
"life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:6.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:6.2"
msgid ""
"“nāmaṃ kho, āvuso, eko anto, rūpaṃ dutiyo anto, viññāṇaṃ majjhe, taṇhā "
"sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“Name, reverends, is one end. Form is the second end. Consciousness is the "
"middle. And craving is the seamstress …"

msgctxt "an6.61:6.3"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.61:6.4"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ parijānāti, "
"abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows … an end of suffering in this very "
"life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.401"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:7.2"
msgid ""
"“cha kho, āvuso, ajjhattikāni āyatanāni eko anto, cha bāhirāni āyatanāni "
"dutiyo anto, viññāṇaṃ majjhe, taṇhā sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“The six interior sense fields, reverends, are one end. The six exterior "
"sense fields are the second end. Consciousness is the middle. And craving is "
"the seamstress …"

msgctxt "an6.61:7.3"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an6.61:7.4"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ parijānāti, "
"abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows … an end of suffering in this very "
"life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:8.2"
msgid ""
"“sakkāyo kho, āvuso, eko anto, sakkāyasamudayo dutiyo anto, sakkāyanirodho "
"majjhe, taṇhā sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“Identity, reverends, is one end. The origin of identity is the second end. "
"The cessation of identity is the middle. And craving is the seamstress,"

msgctxt "an6.61:8.3"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr "for craving weaves one to rebirth in this or that state of existence."

#. VAR: parijānanto → sabbatthapi evameva
msgctxt "an6.61:8.4"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ parijānāti, "
"abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti. (6)"
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows what should be directly known and "
"completely understands what should be completely understood. Knowing and "
"understanding thus they make an end of suffering in this very life.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:9.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When this was said, one of the mendicants said to the senior mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.61:9.2"
msgid "“byākataṃ kho, āvuso, amhehi sabbeheva yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ."
msgstr "“Each of us has spoken from the heart."

msgctxt "an6.61:9.3"
msgid ""
"Āyāmāvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato "
"etamatthaṃ ārocessāma."
msgstr "Come, reverends, let’s go to the Buddha, and inform him about this."

msgctxt "an6.61:9.4"
msgid "Yathā no bhagavā byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti. (7)"
msgstr "As he answers, so we’ll remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:10.1"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho therā bhikkhū tassa bhikkhuno paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” those senior mendicants replied."

msgctxt "an6.61:10.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho therā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then those senior mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "an6.61:10.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho therā bhikkhū yāvatako ahosi sabbeheva saddhiṃ "
"kathāsallāpo, taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed. They asked,"

msgctxt "an6.61:10.4"
msgid "“Kassa nu kho, bhante, subhāsitan”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, who has spoken well?”"

msgctxt "an6.61:10.5"
msgid ""
"“Sabbesaṃ vo, bhikkhave, subhāsitaṃ pariyāyena, api ca yaṃ mayā sandhāya "
"bhāsitaṃ pārāyane metteyyapañhe:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, you’ve all spoken well in a way. However, this is what I was "
"referring to in ‘The Way to the Beyond’, in ‘The Questions of Metteyya’ when "
"I said:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:11.1"
msgid "‘Yo ubhonte viditvāna,"
msgstr "‘The sage has known both ends,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.61:11.2"
msgid "majjhe mantā na lippati;"
msgstr "and is not stuck in the middle."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.61:11.3"
msgid "Taṃ brūmi mahāpurisoti,"
msgstr "He is a great man, I declare,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.61:11.4"
msgid "sodha sibbinimaccagā’ti."
msgstr "he has escaped the seamstress here.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.402"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an6.61:12.1"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an6.61:12.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho therā bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an6.61:12.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

msgctxt "an6.61:12.4"
msgid ""
"“phasso kho, bhikkhave, eko anto, phassasamudayo dutiyo anto, phassanirodho "
"majjhe, taṇhā sibbinī;"
msgstr ""
"“Contact, mendicants, is one end. The origin of contact is the second end. "
"The cessation of contact is the middle. And craving is the seamstress,"

msgctxt "an6.61:12.5"
msgid "taṇhā hi naṃ sibbati tassa tasseva bhavassa abhinibbattiyā."
msgstr "for craving weaves one to rebirth in this or that state of existence."

msgctxt "an6.61:12.6"
msgid ""
"Ettāvatā kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānāti, pariññeyyaṃ "
"parijānāti, abhiññeyyaṃ abhijānanto pariññeyyaṃ parijānanto diṭṭheva dhamme "
"dukkhassantakaro hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant directly knows what should be directly known and "
"completely understands what should be completely understood. Knowing and "
"understanding thus they make an end of suffering in this very life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.61:12.7"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
